description.plain:
Jhené Aiko Efuru Chilombo (born March 16, 1988) started her career under the moniker Jhené Aiko when she was 13 with the music group B2K. She explained how she later opted out of the deal to go back to high school and have her daughter Namiko in an interview back in July 2012 with Lozza Music:

I was signed with Sony/EPIC when I was 12 years old and got a release from them when I was about 15 or 16 to focus on school. I started writing more and I had a child who’s now three years old.

After the failed release of her debut album, My Name Is Jhené back in 2003, Jhené released her debut mixtape, Sailing Soul(s) on March 16, 2011.

Following the release of her EP, Sail Out in 2013, she finally released her long-awaited debut studio album in 2014 titled Souled Out.

In 2017, Jhené released her second studio album, Trip on September 22, 2017, with an accompanying short film and a poetry book.

annotatable.title: The Worst

body.plain:
From the “Sail Out” EP, this song was released January 14, 2014 as the album’s second official single through ARTium and Def Jam Recordings. It offers a sample of the 2003 single “Excuse Me Miss” by Jay Z.

The song’s lyrics explore Aiko’s regret towards falling in love with someone not right for her. It peaked at #43 on the Billboard Hot 100. The accompanying video directed by Danny Williams depicts the aftermath of the murder of Aiko’s boyfriend (presumably because of his mistreatment of her described in the song).

body.plain:
Jhené Aiko reunites with her ex-boyfriend, Big Sean, on “None of Your Concern,” where they reflect on their failed relationship and attempt to move on. This is the ex-couple’s second collaboration of 2019, following Sean’s July track, “Single Again.” Both tracks seemingly deal with the repercussions of their past relationship and each symbolize a different phase of their paths towards getting past their breakup.

The song was released along with accompanying visuals on November 15, 2019. The video features Jhené and Sean in various parts of Hawaii.

body.plain:
“Triggered” serves as Jhené Aiko’s first official single from her upcoming 2019 album. This freestyle addressed numerous different topics, including her past relationships.

While she has publicly denied that this is a diss track, it seems to be sending shots at Detroit rapper Big Sean, who she broke up with in March 2019.

She announced the song on Twitter on Tuesday, May 7th, 2019.

songs.full_title: New Balance by Jhené Aiko

annotatable.link_title: New Balance by Jhené Aiko
annotatable.title: New Balance

body.plain:
On Aug. 14 ‘16, Jhene Aiko tweeted out a Tumblr link to what initially seemed to be a romantic poem.

https://twitter.com/JheneAiko/status/764898489708875776?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw

Shortly after though, her partner in the newly formed music duo TWENTY88 and rumored love interest Big Sean made it clear these were lyrics to a song he’d already heard.

https://twitter.com/BigSean/status/764900782688854017?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw

A few hours later, Aiko finally released the song and even acknowledged a tweet suggesting the overture was directed at none other than Big Sean.

https://twitter.com/JheneAiko/status/764965728684507136?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw

This all comes a few days after reports that Aiko was officially ending her marriage with respected producer and Kid Cudi collaborator Dot Da Genius.

On “New Balance,” Aiko seemingly professes her new found love for Big Sean, and reputes the people that have criticized her divorce.

body.plain:
Written by Jhene Aiko

“ i was born on March 16th . 3:16 is a popular bible verse that i believe in… but on the contrary… 3am is a dark hour… strong urges to want to leap off a building… this song is about real life depression, addiction, destructive love and suicide… it was a dark time for me + i smoked a lot of weed while i wrote it ”


jhene aiko



to be featured as track #6 on Jhené’s upcoming EP “Sail Out,” out everywhere on November 12th.

This video from the Fader.com explains the meaning of the song:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&v=2fyADbWojv4

body.plain:
“Spotless Mind” was a never before heard song that Jhené performed live for the first time at Coachella 2014.

The CDQ version of the song leaked on August 18th, a day before it was due to be released as a free download for anyone who pre-ordered her début album Souled Out on iTunes.

body.plain:
Jhené Aiko Efuru Chilombo (born March 16, 1988) started her career under the moniker Jhené Aiko when she was 13 with the music group B2K. She explained how she later opted out of the deal to go back to high school and have her daughter Namiko in an interview back in July 2012 with Lozza Music:

I was signed with Sony/EPIC when I was 12 years old and got a release from them when I was about 15 or 16 to focus on school. I started writing more and I had a child who’s now three years old.

After the failed release of her debut album, My Name Is Jhené back in 2003, Jhené released her debut mixtape, Sailing Soul(s) on March 16, 2011.

Following the release of her EP, Sail Out in 2013, she finally released her long-awaited debut studio album in 2014 titled Souled Out.

In 2017, Jhené released her second studio album, Trip on September 22, 2017, with an accompanying short film and a poetry book.
